  "critical": false,
  "description": "Domestic pigeons (Columba livia) raised for squab meat (26-30 day old juveniles) and guano fertilizer. Pigeons are self-feeding foragers requiring minimal supplemental feed, and squab reaches market weight (350-500g dressed) in under a month. Pigeon guano is one of the richest natural fertilizers (high NPK).",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Near-zero feed cost if allowed to forage. Squab production cycle is under 30 days. Guano is premium fertilizer.",
